With Go 1.16, running mage (e.g. here in {{lib-metadata}} repo) produces this error:

{noformat}$ go run .mage/mage.go -d .mage -w . -debug
DEBUG: 09:04:23.310866 getting all non-mage files in .mage
DEBUG: 09:04:23.319071 found non-mage files 
DEBUG: 09:04:23.319083 getting all files plus mage files
DEBUG: 09:04:23.326719 time to scan for Magefiles: 15.898137ms
No .go files marked with the mage build tag in this directory.
exit status 1{noformat}

The lack of files within mage comes from [this command|https://github.com/magefile/mage/blob/07afc7d24f4d6d6442305d49552f04fbda5ccb3e/mage/main.go#L473] (run in {{.mage}} sub-directory and produces zero results):

{noformat}go list -tags=mage -e -f '{{join .GoFiles "||"}}'{noformat}

comments.body:
It’s because of this [https://github.com/golang/go/issues/43985|https://github.com/golang/go/issues/43985|smart-link] 

This has been mentioned in the Go 1.16 release notes:

{quote}In module mode, the {{go}} command now disallows import paths that include non-ASCII characters or path elements with a leading dot character ({{.}}). Module paths with these characters were already disallowed (see [+Module paths and versions+|https://golang.org/ref/mod#go-mod-file-ident]), so this change affects only paths within module subdirectories.{quote}
